TITLE: Huawei's revenue barely rose in the third quarter, despite phone and car sales growth
SUMMARY: Chinese tech giant Huawei reported revenue figures Friday that showed only a 1% increase in the third quarter from a year ago, according to CNBC calculations.

TITLE: UPS stock falls after delivery giant cuts revenue outlook
SUMMARY: UPS reported third quarter earnings and warned of persistent global economic uncertainty.

TITLE: Amazon reports better-than-expected results, as revenue jumps 13%
SUMMARY: Amazon reported earnings after the bell. Here are the results.

TITLE: Ford misses Wall Street's Q3 expectations, pulls guidance due to UAW strike, pending deal
SUMMARY: Ford Motor reported earnings after the bell. Its EV unit lost more than $1.3 billion in the quarter.

TITLE: Intel stock rises on earnings beat and strong revenue guidance
SUMMARY: Intel CFO David Zinsner said in a statement that the company's earnings per share benefited from controlling expenses.

TITLE: Chipotle Mexican Grill easily tops earnings estimates, as higher prices help offset food inflation
SUMMARY: Beef and queso costs rose this quarter, largely offsetting last year's menu price hikes.

TITLE: Marlboro maker Altria reports declining revenue, citing competition from illicit e-vapor products
SUMMARY: The Marlboro maker said domestic cigarette shipment volume fell 11.6%, primarily driven by industry declines and competition from illicit e-vapor products.

TITLE: Southwest slows 2024 growth as travel demand moderates
SUMMARY: Southwest's net income in the third quarter dropped 30% from a year earlier.

TITLE: Bristol Myers Squibb earnings top estimates even as top-selling drug fights generic competition
SUMMARY: Bristol Myers Squibb’s revenue was in line with estimates, but fell slightly from the same period last year due to lower sales of blood cancer drug Revlimid.

TITLE: Comcast sinks despite profit beat, as broadband subscribers slip and ad revenue slumps
SUMMARY: Comcast revenue and earnings both topped analyst estimates as theme park sales rose, and Peacock added 4 million subscribers.

TITLE: Merck results beat expectations on strong Keytruda sales, surprise Covid drug growth
SUMMARY: Merck's revenue and earnings beat expectations, and it hiked its sales forecast while lowering its profit outlook.

TITLE: Meta beats on top and bottom lines as digital ad recovery pushes revenue up 23%
SUMMARY: Meta reported better-than-expected third-quarter results on Wednesday, but finance chief Susan Li offered cautionary comments about the ad market

TITLE: IBM software sales up 8% as the company beats on top and bottom lines
SUMMARY: IBM reiterated its revenue and profit forecast for the full year, having completed its acquisition of cloud cost management software maker Apptio in August.

TITLE: Life Time stock plummets as company spends more on premium fitness experience
SUMMARY: Life Time said the investments — including new pickleball courts and personal training programs — have helped drive member engagement at its clubs.

TITLE: Boeing cuts 737 Max delivery forecast as production issues dent third-quarter results
SUMMARY: Boeing also posted a wider-than-expected loss for the third quarter.

TITLE: Beer giant Heineken posts sales hit on Russia exit, higher prices
SUMMARY: The Dutch brewer sold its Russia operations for one euro in August, while consumers globally were deterred by higher beer prices.

TITLE: Deutsche Bank shares surge 7% after net profit beats expectations
SUMMARY: Deutsche Bank reported a third-quarter net profit of 1.031 billion euros ($1.06 billion), slightly beating expectations.

TITLE: Alphabet shares drop as cloud miss overshadows better-than-expected overall results
SUMMARY: Alphabet reported earnings after the bell. Here are the results.

TITLE: Microsoft ticks up on faster cloud growth and hopeful revenue forecast
SUMMARY: Microsoft delivered stronger results than expected as Azure growth accelerated, and the forecast suggested stability.

TITLE: Snap shares seesaw amid concerns about the war's effect on advertising
SUMMARY: Snap reported third-quarter earnings and said its sales have jumped 5% year over year to $1.19 billion.

TITLE: Coca-Cola beats earnings estimates, raises outlook as volume grows despite price hikes
SUMMARY: Coca-Cola's stock has fallen 15% this year, dragging its market value down to about $234 billion.

TITLE: GM tops Q3 expectations but pulls full-year guidance due to mounting UAW strike costs
SUMMARY: GM has been navigating ongoing strikes by the United Auto Workers after the union and Detroit automakers failed to reach labor deals by a Sept. 14 deadline.

TITLE: World’s largest sovereign wealth fund loses $34 billion as all asset classes fall in third quarter
SUMMARY: Norway's $1.4 trillion sovereign wealth fund on Tuesday reported losses of 2.1% in the third quarter, as all asset classes fell in value.

TITLE: Barclays down 6.5% after warning of fourth-quarter cost-cutting charges
SUMMARY: Barclays on Tuesday reported a net profit of £1.27 billion ($1.56 billion) for the third quarter, slightly ahead of expectations.

TITLE: American Airlines posts third-quarter loss and trims 2023 profit forecast
SUMMARY: American Airlines posted a third-quarter loss on Thursday and trimmed its profit forecast for the year.

TITLE: Nokia to cut up to 14,000 jobs after 69% profit plunge
SUMMARY: Nokia said it would cut up to 14,000 jobs as part of a cost cutting plan following third quarter earnings that plunged.

TITLE: World's largest chipmaker TSMC sees biggest drop in profit in nearly five years
SUMMARY: TSMC posted a third quarter profit of NT$211 billion – its largest profit decline since first quarter 2019 – as weak demand for consumer electronics persists.

TITLE: Tesla CEO Elon Musk sounds pessimistic note about economy on earnings call
SUMMARY: During the company's earnings call, CEO Elon Musk said the company's focused on making its cars more affordable.

TITLE: Netflix profit beats expectations, ad-tier subscriptions rise
SUMMARY: Netflix reported earnings after the bell. Here are the results.

TITLE: Morgan Stanley shares fall over 6% as wealth management results disappoint
SUMMARY: Morgan Stanley shares fell even as the bank posted better-than-expected profits.
